  "poem": {
    "content": "A ginger cat upon the bench,\nWatches the world, a simple sketch.\nPeople pass, a hurried trade,\nOf smiles and frowns, a life displayed.\n\nThe outer reaches, cold and vast,\nWhere lonely ships forever cast\nTheir shadows, in an endless orbit,\nA silent film, a cosmic forfeit.\n\nA novel read beneath the leaf,\nHides secrets, sorrow, disbelief.\nA tagged ambition starts to wane,\nAs dreams decrease, like falling rain.\n\nThe plan to execute, they say,\nChanges with the view each day.\nAlso, a wish, kept close and deep\nAs sleep,\nThat even in this shadowed place,\nA new star rises to displace\nThe endless night, a brighter gleam,\nTo wake us from this novel dream.",
